        <div class="col-md-9 nohighlight member-container">
            <h2 class="memberLink col-md-9" id="member-link-a36210c3-001a-406a-af13-5620730f1e37">
                Mr. Silverman
            </h2>
        </div>
            <div class="col-md-3 hidden-sm hidden-xs right-column ">
            <a href="#contribution-a36210c3-001a-406a-af13-5620730f1e37" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
               data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
               data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1947-11-06/debates/efb1aa5d-3338-442d-adcb-849fbee7fd15/PublicAppointments(MinistersRecommendations)#contribution-a36210c3-001a-406a-af13-5620730f1e37">
                <div class="share-icon">&nbsp;</div><span class="share-text">Share</span>
            </a>
        </div>

    


    <div class="inner">
        <div class="col-md-9 contribution content-container">



<p class="">Surely, the meaning of the word "nepotism" is that people are appointed to offices not by reason of their merits—[HON. MEMBERS: "Hear, hear"] —but in order that a Minister may show favour to some members of his family, or to some other personal connections—</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
